SUMMARY:Wellness Walk
DTSTAMP:20260616T175128Z
DTSTART:20260623T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Laura Conely of Urban Paths for a fun evening as we explor
	e the trails and beauty of Hermann Park on a guided 3-mile experience. All
	 are invited to this conversationally paced walk\; friendly pups on leash 
	are welcome too! \nThis event is free\, but registration is required and s
	pace is limited. Sign up HERE. Participants will meet outside the McGovern
	 Centennial Gardens\, located at 1500 Hermann Drive\, with parking availab
	le in adjacent Lot C. \nLaura Conely is the founder of Urban Paths\, a wal
	king wellness company. As a certified teacher and coach\, she leads guided
	 Wellness Walks that bring individuals of all ages and fitness levels toge
	ther to experience the profound health benefits of: Nature\, Art\, Movemen
	t\, and Connection.\n\nhttps://hermannpark.org/event/wellness-walk-8/\n\nF
	rom Hermann Park Conservancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/wellness-walk-8/
LOCATION:TX
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hermann-park
CATEGORIES:Hermann Park Conservancy
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp
 -content/uploads/2026/02/Pitch-in-at-Hermann-Park-e1772040133699.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/0
 2/Pitch-in-at-Hermann-Park-e1772040133699.jpg
UID:uJt2SwOOJuI3gcQFmAfzy
SUMMARY:Pitch in at Hermann Park
DTSTAMP:20260616T175128Z
DTSTART:20260624T083000Z
DESCRIPTION:Give the Park you love a little extra care\, and help us get re
	ady for the world! Join us for “Pitch in at Hermann Park\,” a hands-on vol
	unteer series where community members of all ages come together to help ca
	re for Houston’s most cherished green spaces. \nWe’re proud to work alongs
	ide FWC26Houston and Harris County–Houston Sports Authority in the Impact 
	Houston 26 efforts to elevate the local environmental action on a global s
	tage and build a lasting\, positive legacy for our city. \nYou’ll work alo
	ngside Conservancy staff on simple but meaningful projects like mulching\,
	 planting\, and litter cleanup — the kind of small efforts that make a big
	 impact for visitors\, wildlife\, and the health of the Park. \nThis volun
	teer session will be in the Heart of the Park (6104 Hermann Park Drive\, H
	ouston Texas 77030). Volunteers will meet at the Pedal Boat Kiosk. Enter t
	hrough Lot G (near the Zoo) or Lot E and park in Lot F.  Walk up the concr
	ete sidewalk to the Pedal Boat Kiosk\, and we will be watching for your gr
	oup. \nNo experience is needed — just comfortable clothes\, closed-toe sho
	es\, and a willingness to help. We’ll provide the tools\, guidance\, and a
	 great way to spend your morning outdoors while meeting new people and giv
	ing back to the community. \nWhether you come with friends\, family\, cowo
	rkers\, or on your own\, your time truly matters here. Help us welcome the
	 world to Hermann Park! \nSIGN UP HERE. \nWeather:   Volunteer projects ar
	e rain or shine\, unless there is severe weather. Cancellations due to sev
	ere weather will be sent via text/email at least 1 hour before your shift.
	 Use your best judgment when traveling in inclement weather. \nQuestions? 
	Email volunteer@hermannpark.org or call 713-524-5876. Remember\, we are of
	ten out in the field\, so email is the preferred method of getting in touc
	h!\n\nhttps://hermannpark.org/event/pitch-in-at-hermann-park-13/\n\nFrom H
	ermann Park Conservancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/pitch-in-at-hermann-park-13/
LOCATION:Lake Plaza
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hermann-park
CATEGORIES:Hermann Park Conservancy
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
